newCollectionInstance

@Deprecated
public static java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object> newCollectionInstance(java.lang.Class<?> collectionClass)
Deprecated. (scheduled to be removed in 1.5) use Data.newCollectionInstance(Type)

Returns a new instance of the given collection class.

If a concrete collection class in the The class of the returned collection instance depends on the input collection class as follows (first that matches):

  • null or ArrayList is an instance of the collection class: returns an ArrayList
  • Concrete subclass of Collection: returns an instance of that collection class
  • HashSet is an instance of the collection class: returns a HashSet
  • TreeSet is an instance of the collection class: returns a TreeSet

Parameters:
collectionClass - collection class or null for ArrayList.
Returns:
new collection instance
